rv_baremetal-boot-plan9-riscv64-wdt: watchdog feeding ported to objtype=riscv64 - completes the working base (GPIO + UART + watchdog + real calls)

WHAT THIS IS
------------
Port of rv_baremetal-boot-linux-wdt-clk-mode's wdt.c onto Plan9
objtype=riscv64, alongside the already-verified gpio/uart code carried
over unchanged from rv_baremetal-boot-plan9-riscv64-uart. First
multi-file build in this project's Plan9 side: main.c and wdt.c are
compiled and linked as separate objects (see mkfile).

main() feeds `riscv_wdt` (the C906 core's own watchdog, already armed
by U-Boot/SPL before this code gets control) once per LED-toggle tick -
a deliberately conservative first test: `wdt_main_*` and
`wdt_riscv_enable/disable` are ported and available but not called from
the loop, so if feeding doesn't actually work the failure mode is the
board resetting on its own on a fixed timer, which is itself the test
result, not a hang to debug blind.

PORTING NOTES (useful checklist for the next port)
-----------------------------------------------------
  - start.s needs `MOVW $setSB(SB), R3` before stack setup, same as
    rv_baremetal-boot-plan9-riscv64-uart - wdt.c and main.c both
    reference small globals/constants that need it.
  - The one real source change from the GCC original: wdt_timeout_map's
    C99 designated initializers (`[0] = 0x0, ...`) aren't supported by
    ic (an ANSI/K&R-era compiler) - rewritten as a plain positional
    array, same values in the same order.
  - PUT32/GET32 used instead of mmio.h's volatile-pointer helpers.
  - `unsigned long` behaves like plain 32-bit `unsigned int` in this
    compiler (TLONG uses the same AMOVW codegen path as TINT, not
    widened for riscv64) - only pointers (TIND) are genuinely 64-bit
    here, so wdt_feed_at/wdt_enable_at/wdt_disable_at's `base` parameter
    is `unsigned int`, matching PUT32/GET32's own signature, not
    `unsigned long` like the GCC original.

STATUS
------
Confirmed on real hardware: LED blinks, UART prints continuously, and
the board does not reset (previously reset roughly every minute when
riscv_wdt went unfed) - the watchdog is genuinely being kicked, not
just compiling without error. This folder is the completed goal: a
Plan9 riscv64 bare-metal base with working watchdog, UART, GPIO, and
real (non-inlined) function calls. See the BinOutput project's memory:
plan9-riscv64-wdt-uart-base.

Also see rv_baremetal-boot-plan9-riscv64-test-* for a follow-on
synthetic compiler test suite (switch, div/mod, function pointers,
array indexing, 64-bit arithmetic, structs) built on top of this base
to shake out any further compiler bugs - all passed.

BUILD
-----
mk (produces main.out and main.bin from start.s + main.c + wdt.c;
main.bin is the flashable headerless output, built with -s to strip
Plan9 symbols). objtype=riscv64 is set at the top of the mkfile.
